First Solar Rises on Sale of Topaz Project to Buffett

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-12-07T14:37:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/first-solar-climbs-after-selling-2-billion-project-to-buffet.html
(Corrects spelling of name in headline.)  First Solar Inc. (FSLR) , the world’s largest
maker of thin-film panels, rose in early New York trading after
agreeing to sell its $2 billion Topaz solar farm in Southern
California to  Warren Buffett ’s MidAmerican Energy Holdings.  First Solar climbed 6.6 percent to $49.17 at 9:05 a.m.
Before today, the shares had declined 65 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Martin in New York at 
 cmartin11@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 